    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Profits Rise 85% At Reader's Digest</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Peter Beller</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Beller, Peter</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Reader's Digest announces 85 percent hike in fourth-quarter operating profits and 54 percent gain in fiscal year ending June 30 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Reader's Digest, based in Chappaqua, announced an 85% increase in fourth-quarter operating profits compared with last year and a 54% increase for the fiscal year, ended June 30. In 1999 the company's profits increased 67%.</p>
        <p>This year the company saw its first full-year revenue increase since 1996.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Reader's Digest, based in Chappaqua, announced an 85% increase in fourth-quarter operating profits compared with last year and a 54% increase for the fiscal year, ended June 30. In 1999 the company's profits increased 67%.</p>
        <p>This year the company saw its first full-year revenue increase since 1996.</p>
        <p>After years of decline, the company has experienced earnings growth in the nine quarters for which Thomas O. Ryder has been chairman. He has trimmed unprofitable operations and focused on the book division.</p>
        <p>Peter Beller</p>
        <p>IN BUSINESS</p>
      </block>
